While it may appear he is a class prefect writing down the names of his unruly and disruptive classmates, it turns out he's not.He was part of the Homeland Series outreach programme by US-based artist Solomon Adufah, which later inspired a series of paintings."Jake was one of the children I taught in Ghana. He was always gentle and quiet. Ever present in class and was eager to learn every day," Adufah wrote on Instagram alongside the now-famous picture of JakeSo there you have it: he was learning how to express himself through art.But according to social media users, his face depicts a number of sidesplitting scenarios and characters.Now try not to roll on the floor bursting with laughter: Find the hottest celebrity and entertainment news on TshisaLIVE or follow TshisaLIVE on Facebook and Twitter.